of%20negotiations%2C%20Prime%20Minister%20Benjamin%20Netanyahu%20reached%20an%20agreement%20with%20the%20centrist%20opposition%20party%20National%20Unity.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAs%20part%20of%20the%20agreement%2C%20former%20Defense%20Minister%20Benny%20Gantz%20and%20his%20colleagues%20Gadi%20Eisenkot%2C%20Gideon%20Sa'ar%2C%20Hili%20Tropper%2C%20and%20Yifat%20Shasha-Biton%20will%20be%20ministers%20in%20the%20new%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBenny%20Gantz%20will%20join%20the%20war%20cabinet%20with%20Netanyahu%20and%20Defense%20Minister%20Yoav%20Gallant.%20Former%20chief%20of%20staff%20of%20the%20Israeli%20army%2C%20Gadi%20Eisenkot%2C%20and%20Strategic%20Affairs%20Minister%20Ron%20Dermer%20will%20assume%20observer%20status.%20The%20new%20Israeli%20emergency%20government%20has%20been%20established%20for%20the%20duration%20of%20the%20war%20with%20Hamas%20and%20possible%20other%20regional%20actors.%20It%20does%20not%20have%20any%20authority%20to%20legislate%20on%20issues%20not%20related%20directly%20to%20the%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20broad%20emergency%20government%20has%20been%20warmly%20welcomed%20by%20large%20parts%20of%20the%20Israeli%20population.%20In%20a%20televised%20joint%20statement%20after%20the%20formation%20of%20the%20new%20government%2C%20Netanyahu%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BWe%20set%20aside%20every%20other%20consideration%20because%20the%20fate%20of%20the%20country%20is%20at%20stake%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBenny%20Gantz%20added%2C%20%26quot%3BUs%20standing%20here%20shoulder-to-shoulder%20is%20a%20clear%20message%20to%20our%20enemy%2C%20and%20more%20importantly%2C%20a%20message%20to%20all%20the%20citizens%20of%20Israel%20-%20we%20are%20all%20together%2C%20we%20are%20all%20mobilizing%2C%20we%20are%20all%20being%20mobilized.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20Yoav%20Gallant%20declared%20that%20the%20new%20Israeli%20government%20would%20%26quot%3Bwipe%20Hamas%20out%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIntensifying%20pressure%20on%20Gaza%2C%20Defense%20Minister%20Yoav%20Gallant%20ordered%20a%20blockade%20earlier%20this%20week%2C%20including%20a%20ban%20on%20food%2C%20electricity%2C%20water%20and%20fuel%20to%20the%20region.%20Early%20Wednesday%20afternoon%2C%20the%20Gaza%20power%20plant%20stopped%20working%20due%20to%20lack%20of%20fuel%2C%20cutting%20off%20the%20electricity%20in%20the%20entire%20area.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Rafah%20border%20crossing%20between%20Gaza%20and%20Egypt%20was%20closed%20Wednesday%20after%20it%20was%20hit%20by%20Israeli%20air%20raids%20twice.%20According%20to%20Israeli%20Channel%2012%2C%20Israel%20wanted%20to%20prevent%20Hamas%20from%20smuggling%20fuel%20into%20Gaza.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EUN%20Secretary-General%20Antonio%20Guterres%20criticized%20Israel%20for%20its%20blockade%20of%20Gaza%20and%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BLife-saving%20supplies%2C%20including%20fuel%2C%20food%20and%20water%2C%20must%20be%20allowed%20into%20Gaza.%20We%20need%20rapid%20and%20unhindered%20humanitarian%20access%20now.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EEuropean%20Union%20foreign%20policy%20chief%20Josep%20Borrell%20said%20Israel%20was%20breaking%20international%20law%20with%20its%20total%20blockade%20of%20Gaza.%20The%20blockade%20is%20seen%20by%20many%20as%20collective%20punishment%20of%20the%20entire%20population%20in%20Gaza.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EEgypt%20confirmed%20on%20Wednesday%20that%20it%20is%20working%20with%20the%20United%20States%20to%20provide%20humanitarian%20aid%20to%20Gaza%20via%20the%20Rafah%20border.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20Egypt%20rejects%20a%20so-called%20%26quot%3Bsafe%20corridor%26quot%3B%20to%20enable%20Palestinians%20to%20leave%20Gaza.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Israeli%20bombardment%20of%20Gaza%20escalated%20late%20Wednesday.%20According%20to%20the%20Palestinian%20Ministry%20of%20Health%20in%20Gaza%2C%2051%20Palestinians%20were%20killed%20in%20just%20one%20hour.%20The%20overall%20deaths%20in%20Gaza%20has%20crossed%201%2C200%20while%20almost%206%2C000%20have%20been%20wounded.%20At%20least%203%2C40%2C000%20of%20Gaza's%202.3%20million%20inhabitants%20are%20now%20internally%20displaced.%20According%20to%20the%20UN%2C%2065%20per%20cent%20are%20in%20shelters%20such%20as%20UN%20schools.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Palestinian%20Ministry%20of%20Foreign%20Affairs%20says%20Israeli%20air%20strikes%20have%20destroyed%20more%20than%2022%2C600%20residential%20units%20and%2010%20health%20facilities.%20Also%2C%2048%20schools%20have%20been%20damaged.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOn%20Wednesday%20evening%2C%20a%20siren%20was%20heard%20in%20the%20northern%20Israeli%20city%20of%20Haifa%20for%20the%20first%20time%20since%20the%20latest%20escalation.%20At%20first%2C%20unofficial%20reports%20suggested%20that%20an%20unknown%20number%20of%20Lebanese%20Hezbollah%20fighters%20had%20managed%20to%20enter%20the%20city%2C%20carried%20by%20paragliders.%20The%20entire%20population%20in%20Haifa%20and%20its%20suburbs%20were%20asked%20to%20stay%20in%2C%20lock%20their%20doors%20and%20shut%20their%20windows.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOne%20Israeli%20TV%20station%20showed%20pictures%20of%20an%20unmanned%20drone%20circling%20the%20sky%20above%20Haifa%2C%20and%20Hamas%20claimed%20responsibility%20for%20firing%20a%20missile%20on%20the%20city.%20Unconfirmed%20reports%20about%20Hezbollah%20paragliders%20in%20the%20mountainous%20Haifa%20area%20created%20some%20fear%20that%20Haifa%20would%20be%20attacked%20the%20same%20way%20as%20the%20smaller%20Israeli%20villages%20outside%20Gaza.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EUS%20President%20Joe%20Biden%20said%20he%20has%20warned%20Iran%20against%20escalating%20the%20conflict%20between%20Hamas%20and%20Israel.%20Both%20Hamas%20and%20Hezbollah%20are%20financed%20by%20Iran%20and%20are%20considered%20Iranian%20regional%20proxies.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20made%20it%20clear%20to%20the%20Iranians%20-%20be%20careful%2C%26quot%3B%20Biden%20said%20during%20a%20meeting%20with%20American%20Jewish%20community%20leaders%20at%20the%20White%20House.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20back-and-forth%20on%20whether%20Egypt%20had%20warned%20Israel%20about%20Hamas'%20intentions%20to%20carry%20out%20a%20comprehensive%20attack%2C%20new%20information%20emerged%20on%20Wednesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EUS%20House%20Foreign%20Affairs%20Committee%20Chair%20Michael%20McCaul%20told%20reporters%20that%20Egypt%20had%20warned%20Israel%20three%20days%20before%20the%20Hamas%20attack%2C%20according%20to%20US%20media.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20know%20that%20Egypt%20had%20warned%20the%20Israelis%20three%20days%20prior%20that%20an%20event%20like%20this%20could%20happen.%20We%20know%20this%20event%20was%20planned%20perhaps%20as%20long%20as%20a%20year%20ago%2C%26quot%3B%20Michael%20McCaul%20stated.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Israeli%20government%20strongly%20denies%20it%20had%20received%20any%20sort%20of%20early%20warning%20about%20an%20imminent%20Hamas%20attack.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Saturday%20morning%20attack%20on%20Israel%20is%20considered%20the%20worst%20in%20the%20nation's%20history%20due%20to%20the%20sheer%20scale%20of%20it.%20Citizens%20are%20still%20coming%20to%20terms%20with%20the%20devastation%20and%20loss%20of%20lives.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIsraeli%20far%20right%20protesters%20rioted%20outside%20one%20of%20Israel's%20main%20hospitals%20as%20a%20Hamas%20member%20was%20treated%20inside.%20The%20rioters%20blocked%20the%20entrance%20to%20the%20hospital%20and%20demanded%20that%20terrorists%20should%20not%20receive%20medical%20treatment%20in%20Israeli%20hospitals.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Allan%20Sorensen%20is%20the%20Middle%20East%20correspondent%20for%20the%20Danish%20daily%20newspaper%20Kristeligt%20Dagblad.)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697095200000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-10%2Fftskaf9g_daily-despatch-5_625x300_12_October_23.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fdaily-despatch-israels-new-wartime-government-gazas-worsening-crisis-4473764%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22With%20all%20signs%20pointing%20at%20the%20Israel-Hamas%20conflict%20turning%20into%20a%20war%20on%20multiple%20fronts%20soon%2C%20a%20new%20emergency%20government%20was%20established%20on%20Wednesday%20afternoon%20in%20Jerusalem.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fdaily-despatch-israels-new-wartime-government-gazas-worsening-crisis-4473764%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Woman%E2%80%99s%20Autonomy%20Over%20Body%20vs%20Right%20to%20Life%20of%20Unborn%20Child%3A%20SC%E2%80%99s%20Split%20Judgment%20Decoded%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F12115952%2FCambios_en_una_adolescente.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20Supreme%20Court%20division%20bench%20comprising%20Justices%20Hima%20Kohli%20and%20B.V.%20Nagarathna%20heard%20the%20Union%20government%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fcentre-seeks-recall-of-scs-order-permitting-married-woman-to-terminate-26-week-pregnancy%5C%22%3Eapplication%20for%20recall%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20its%20October%2010%20order%20directing%20the%20termination%20of%20the%20pregnancy%20of%20a%20married%20woman%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20October%2011.%20The%20bench%2C%20however%2C%20put%20on%20record%20the%20split%20among%20the%20two%20judges%20on%20whether%20the%20woman%E2%80%99s%20right%20to%20seek%20termination%20of%20her%20pregnancy%20could%20be%20recognised%20in%20the%2027th%20week%20of%20gestation.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EJustice%20Kohli%20observed%20that%20her%20judicial%20conscience%20could%20not%20permit%20ending%20the%20life%20of%20the%20unborn%20child%2C%20whose%20delivery%20was%20found%20viable%20by%20the%20Medical%20Board%20of%20the%20All%20India%20Institute%20of%20Medical%20Sciences%20(AIIMS)%2C%20New%20Delhi.%20%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EJustice%20Kohli%20was%20persuaded%20by%20the%20additional%20solicitor%20general%20Aishwarya%20Bhati%2C%20who%20submitted%20that%20the%20bench%2C%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20ought%20not%20to%20be%20concerned%20about%20the%20future%20of%20the%20child%2C%20if%20born%20alive%2C%20but%20should%20only%20decide%20the%20question%20of%20whether%20the%20petitioner-mother%E2%80%99s%20right%20to%20terminate%20her%20pregnancy%20in%20the%2027th%20week%20could%20be%20recognised.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAn%20email%20sent%20by%20one%20of%20the%20doctors%20on%20the%20AIIMS%20Medical%20Board%20pointed%20out%20that%20if%20the%20pregnancy%20is%20to%20be%20terminated%20as%20ordered%20by%20the%20court%20on%20Tuesday%2C%20the%20child%20might%20be%20born%20alive%2C%20but%20with%20the%20risk%20of%20severe%20physical%20or%20mental%20disability.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAlthough%20Justice%20Kohli%20expressed%20her%20disappointment%20that%20the%20doctor%20concerned%20did%20not%20share%20her%20opinion%20ahead%20of%20the%20bench%E2%80%99s%20Tuesday%20order%20directing%20the%20termination%20of%20the%20pregnancy%2C%20she%20was%20inclined%20to%20consider%20it%20in%20order%20to%20recall%20that%20order%2C%20as%20sought%20by%20the%20Union%20government.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20led%20the%20bench%20to%20talk%20afresh%20to%20the%20petitioner-woman%2C%20who%20was%20present%20in%20the%20court%20during%20the%20hearing%20on%20Wednesday.%20Although%20she%20had%20submitted%20an%20affidavit%20saying%20she%20was%20not%20inclined%20to%20continue%20the%20pregnancy%2C%20the%20bench%20confronted%20her%20with%20the%20doctor%E2%80%99s%20opinion%20and%20sought%20to%20know%20whether%20she%20could%20carry%20the%20pregnancy%20for%20one%20or%20two%20more%20weeks%2C%20if%20it%20ensured%20the%20delivery%20of%20a%20healthy%20child.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20her%20husband%20was%20agreeable%20to%20continue%20with%20the%20pregnancy%20for%20one%20or%20two%20more%20weeks%20as%20recommended%20by%20the%20doctor%2C%20the%20petitioner-woman%20clearly%20refused%20to%20do%20so%2C%20and%20this%20convinced%20Justice%20Nagarathna%20that%20her%20right%20over%20her%20body%20must%20be%20respected%20at%20all%20costs.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBhati%2C%20however%2C%20told%20the%20bench%20that%20the%20woman%E2%80%99s%20right%20to%20privacy%20and%20bodily%20autonomy%20ends%20the%20moment%20the%20delivery%20of%20a%20healthy%20child%20is%20found%20viable%20by%20the%20doctors.%20She%20also%20disclosed%20the%20State%E2%80%99s%20readiness%20to%20take%20the%20responsibility%20of%20rearing%20the%20child%2C%20as%20the%20petitioner-mother%20was%20not%20inclined%20to%20do%20so%20because%20of%20the%20limitations%20of%20her%20mental%20health%20and%20of%20the%20family%E2%80%99s%20financial%20means%20to%20support%20another%20child.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EEarlier%2C%20the%20woman%20had%20told%20the%20court%20that%20she%20was%20suffering%20from%20lactational%20amenorrhea%20(which%20causes%20a%20temporary%20absence%20of%20menstruation%20in%20lactating%20mothers)%20and%20post-partum%20depression%20(a%20medical%20condition%20that%20many%20women%20experience%20after%20having%20a%20baby%2C%20with%20feelings%20of%20sadness%2C%20anxiety%20and%20tiredness).%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EJustice%20Nagarathna%2C%20however%2C%20pointed%20to%20the%20petitioner%E2%80%99s%20unwillingness%20to%20continue%20the%20pregnancy%2C%20even%20in%20the%20event%20of%20the%20state%20coming%20forward%20to%20rear%20the%20child%20through%20its%20adoption%20agency.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20result%2C%20while%20Justice%20Kohli%20accepted%20the%20Union%20government%E2%80%99s%20recall%20application%20of%20the%20bench%E2%80%99s%20previous%20order%2C%20Justice%20Nagarathna%20dismissed%20it.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EJustice%20Nagarathna%20also%20expressed%20her%20disappointment%20that%20the%20Union%20government%20mentioned%20the%20recall%20application%20before%20the%20bench%20of%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20after%20the%20hearing%20in%20his%20court%20was%20over%20at%204%20pm%20on%20Tuesday.%20She%20termed%20it%20as%20an%20intra-court%20appeal%2C%20which%20could%20set%20a%20poor%20legal%20precedent%20within%20the%20court.%20Bhati%2C%20however%2C%20apologised%20for%20her%20conduct%2C%20as%20she%20claimed%20she%20could%20not%20mention%20it%20before%20the%20same%20bench%20on%20Tuesday%20because%20she%20was%20arguing%20another%20case%20before%20another%20bench.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EThe%20immediate%20precedent%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EEven%20as%20the%20delay%20caused%20by%20Wednesday%E2%80%99s%20split%20among%20the%20judges%20is%20likely%20to%20be%20of%20concern%20to%20the%20petitioner%2C%20the%20immediate%20precedent%20laid%20down%20by%20the%20court%20in%20another%20case%20could%20have%20been%20followed%20by%20the%20Kohli-Nagarathna%20bench%20in%20this%20case%20as%20well.%20But%20that%20was%20not%20considered%20during%20the%20hearing.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20%3Ci%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Fpdf_upload%2F680-xyz-v-state-of-gujarat-21-aug-2023-490042.pdf%5C%22%3EXYZ%20vs%20State%20of%20Gujarat%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%C2%A0%3C%2Fi%3Ethe%20Supreme%20Court%20bench%20of%20Justices%20Nagarathna%20and%20Ujjal%20Bhuyan%20had%20on%20August%2021%20held%20that%20a%20woman%20alone%20has%20the%20right%20over%20her%20body%20and%20is%20the%20ultimate%20decision-maker%20on%20the%20question%20of%20whether%20she%20wants%20to%20undergo%20an%20abortion.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20this%20case%2C%20the%20report%20of%20the%20medical%20board%2C%20constituted%20by%20the%20Gujarat%20high%20court%2C%20had%20stated%20that%20although%20there%20is%20no%20congenital%20abnormality%20in%20the%20foetus%2C%20the%20medical%20termination%20of%20the%20pregnancy%20could%20only%20be%20done%20if%20the%20court%20permits%2C%20after%20taking%20the%20consent%20of%20the%20appellant%20and%20explaining%20potential%20risk%20to%20maternal%20health.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20noted%20that%20the%20rape%20survivor%20in%20this%20case%20was%20clinically%20fit%20for%20the%20termination%20procedure%20and%20the%20MTP%20would%20not%20adversely%20affect%20child-bearing%20capacity%20and%20her%20general%20health%20in%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAs%20in%20the%20present%20case%2C%20in%3Ci%3E%C2%A0XYZ%20vs%20State%20of%20Gujarat%3C%2Fi%3E%2C%20the%20age%20of%20the%20foetus%20was%20almost%2027%20weeks%20when%20the%20court%20examined%20the%20plea%20for%20termination%20of%20pregnancy.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAgain%20as%20in%20the%20present%20case%2C%20the%20likelihood%20of%20adverse%20impact%20of%20the%20continuance%20of%20the%20pregnancy%20on%20the%20mother%E2%80%99s%20mental%20health%20was%20considered%20a%20relevant%20factor%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%20It%20may%20be%20argued%20that%20in%20%3Cem%3EXYZ%20vs%20State%20of%20Gujarat%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20the%20adverse%20impact%20on%20the%20mental%20health%20of%20the%20mother%20was%20anticipated%20because%20she%20was%20a%20rape%20survivor%20and%20the%20court%20considered%20the%20resultant%20trauma.%20In%20the%20present%20case%2C%20however%2C%20to%20Justice%20Nagarathna%2C%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20petitioner%20is%20a%20married%20woman%2C%20and%20it%20is%20a%20case%20of%20voluntary%20pregnancy%2C%20did%20not%20come%20in%20the%20way%20of%20her%20conclusion%20that%20there%20was%20a%20risk%20of%20adverse%20impact%20on%20her%20mental%20health%20if%20the%20pregnancy%20continued%20beyond%2027%20weeks.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EJustice%20Kohli%2C%20on%20the%20contrary%2C%20was%20persuaded%20by%20the%20Union%20government%E2%80%99s%20contention%20that%20permitting%20the%20MTP%20of%20a%20married%20woman%20beyond%2027%20weeks%20%E2%80%93%20when%20the%20delivery%20of%20a%20healthy%20child%20is%20found%20viable%20by%20the%20doctors%20%E2%80%93%20may%20set%20a%20wrong%20precedent%20and%20that%20there%20may%20be%20others%20who%20could%20exploit%20it%20and%20seek%20MTP%20beyond%2027%20weeks%20on%20the%20ground%20of%20the%20mother%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%9Cmental%20health%20concerns%E2%80%9D%2C%20notwithstanding%20the%20possibility%20of%20giving%20away%20the%20child%20for%20adoption.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHow%20the%20new%20bench%20would%20deal%20with%20these%20delicate%20issues%20would%20be%20interesting%20to%20watch.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697094949000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F12115952%2FCambios_en_una_adolescente.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fwoman-autonomy-body-vs-right-to-life-unborn-child-supreme-court-split-judgment%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Justices%20Hima%20Kohli%20and%20B.V.%20Nagarathna%20split%20on%20a%20married%20woman%E2%80%99s%20right%20to%20abort%20her%20pregnancy%20in%20the%2027th%20week%2C%20leaving%20it%20to%20the%20CJI%20to%20constitute%20another%20bench%20to%20resolve%20the%20issue.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fwoman-autonomy-body-vs-right-to-life-unborn-child-supreme-court-split-judgment%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Alia%20trolled%20for%20her%20latest%20photoshoot%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697094622000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-104363974%2Cimgsize-25364.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Falia-bhatts-latest-photoshoot-leaves-fans-wondering-what-sort-of-poses-are-these%2Farticleshow%2F104