ich%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fworld%2F2023%2Fmar%2F20%2Fisraeli-minister-condemned-claiming-no-such-thing-as-a-palestinian-people-bezalel-smotrich%5C%22%3Eclaimed%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0there%20was%20%E2%80%9Cno%20such%20thing%E2%80%9D%20as%20the%20Palestinian%20people%2C%20while%20the%20US%20State%20Department%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fedition.cnn.com%2F2023%2F08%2F25%2Fworld%2Fisraeli-minister-racist-claim-intl%2Findex.html%5C%22%3Erebuked%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0Ben-Gvir%20for%20his%20%E2%80%9Cracist%2C%20destructive%20comments%E2%80%9D%20about%20the%20supposedly%20inferior%20status%20of%20Palestinians%20in%20the%20West%20Bank.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%C2%A0%3Cem%3EHaaretz%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3Eeditorial%20accused%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20longest-serving%20prime%20minister%20of%20deliberately%20seeking%20a%20violent%20confrontation%20with%20the%20Palestinians%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20past%2C%20Netanyahu%20marketed%20himself%20as%20a%20cautious%20leader%20who%20eschewed%20wars%20and%20multiple%20casualties%20on%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20side.%20After%20his%20victory%20in%20the%20last%20election%2C%20he%20replaced%20this%20caution%20with%20the%20policy%20of%20a%20%E2%80%9Cfully-right%20government%2C%E2%80%9D%20with%20overt%20steps%20taken%20to%20annex%20the%20West%20Bank%2C%20to%20carry%20out%20ethnic%20cleansing%20in%20parts%20of%20the%20Oslo-defined%20Area%20C%2C%20including%20the%20Hebron%20Hills%20and%20the%20Jordan%20Valley.%20This%20also%20included%20a%20massive%20expansion%20of%20settlements%20and%20bolstering%20of%20the%20Jewish%20presence%20on%20Temple%20Mount%2C%20near%20the%20Al-Aqsa%20Mosque%2C%20as%20well%20as%20boasts%20of%20an%20impending%20peace%20deal%20with%20the%20Saudis%20in%20which%20the%20Palestinians%20would%20get%20nothing%2C%20with%20open%20talk%20of%20a%20%E2%80%9Csecond%20Nakba%E2%80%9D%20in%20his%20governing%20coalition.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EHaaretz%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3Ecould%20have%20broadened%20its%20indictment%20to%20include%20the%20Western%20governments%20that%20have%20egged%20on%20Netanyahu%20and%20his%20allies%20at%20every%20turn.%20No%20matter%20how%20often%20the%20leading%20members%20of%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20political%20class%20insisted%20that%20they%20would%20never%20allow%20a%20Palestinian%20state%20to%20come%20into%20being%2C%20the%20United%20States%20and%20the%20most%20powerful%20European%20countries%20continued%20to%20support%20Israel%20unconditionally%20while%20pretending%20that%20there%20was%20some%20kind%20of%20meaningful%20peace%20process%20in%20existence.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20US%20and%20European%20leaders%20did%20everything%20in%20their%20power%20to%20block%20or%20even%20criminalise%20nonviolent%20forms%20of%20pressure%20on%20Israel%2C%20while%20telling%20Palestinians%20that%20they%20must%20not%20under%20any%20circumstances%20use%20violent%20methods%20against%20the%20occupation%20of%20their%20land.%20Now%20the%20same%20leaders%20have%20given%20Netanyahu%20a%20blank%20check%20to%20wage%20war%20on%20Gaza%2C%20when%20they%20know%20from%20past%20experience%20that%20this%20will%20result%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.middleeasteye.net%2Fnews%2Fisrael-palestine-war-gaza-civilian-buildings-bombed%5C%22%3Emassive%2C%20lethal%20violence%20against%20civilians%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Csection%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBurning%20Bridges%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ELet%E2%80%99s%20remember%20how%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20Western%20allies%20have%20responded%20to%20various%20forms%20of%20nonviolent%20action%20by%20Palestinians%20and%20their%20supporters%20in%20recent%20years.%20In%202021%2C%20the%20Palestinian%20Authority%20(PA)%20asked%20the%20International%20Criminal%20Court%20(ICC)%20to%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Flaw%2F2021%2Fmar%2F03%2Ficc-open-formal-investigation-war-crimes-palestine%5C%22%3Einvestigate%20alleged%20Israeli%20war%20crimes%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20occupied%20territories%2C%20including%20the%20attack%20on%20Gaza%20in%202014.%20The%20US%20government%20immediately%20condemned%20the%20move%2C%20and%20Joe%20Biden%E2%80%99s%20Secretary%20of%20State%20Antony%20Blinken%20issued%20the%20following%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.state.gov%2Fthe-united-states-opposes-the-icc-investigation-into-the-palestinian-situation%2F%5C%22%3Estatement%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20United%20States%20believes%20a%20peaceful%2C%20secure%20and%20more%20prosperous%20future%20for%20the%20people%20of%20the%20Middle%20East%20depends%20on%20building%20bridges%20and%20creating%20new%20avenues%20for%20dialogue%20and%20exchange%2C%20not%20unilateral%20judicial%20actions%20that%20exacerbate%20tensions%20and%20undercut%20efforts%20to%20advance%20a%20negotiated%20two-state%20solution.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWe%20will%20continue%20to%20uphold%20our%20strong%20commitment%20to%20Israel%20and%20its%20security%2C%20including%20by%20opposing%20actions%20that%20seek%20to%20target%20Israel%20unfairly.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20statement%20was%20a%20calculated%20insult%20to%20the%20intelligence%20of%20those%20who%20had%20to%20read%20it.%20Blinken%20knows%20perfectly%20well%20that%20there%20are%20no%20%E2%80%9Cefforts%20to%20advance%20a%20negotiated%20two-state%20solution%E2%80%9D%20that%20might%20be%20%E2%80%9Cundercut%E2%80%9D%20by%20an%20ICC%20investigation.%20In%20practice%2C%20the%20Biden%20administration%20wants%20Israel%20to%20be%20shielded%20from%20any%20legal%20accountability%20for%20its%20actions%20from%20here%20to%20the%20end%20of%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20formation%20of%20Netanyahu%E2%80%99s%20new%20government%20with%20his%20partners%20Smotrich%20and%20Ben-Gvir%2C%20Blinken%20told%20a%20J%20Street%20conference%20in%20December%202022%20that%20US%20support%20for%20Israel%20was%20%E2%80%9Csacrosanct.%E2%80%9D%20As%20Peter%20Beinart%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjewishcurrents.org%2Ffor-the-biden-administration-there-are-no-red-lines-on-israel%5C%22%3Enoted%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Blinken%E2%80%99s%20speech%20gave%20Netanyahu%20a%20green%20light%20to%20do%20whatever%20he%20wanted%20in%20the%20occupied%20territories%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Csection%3E%20%3Cp%3EBlinken%20didn%E2%80%99t%20even%20pledge%20to%20undo%20the%20gratuitous%20humiliations%20imposed%20on%20the%20Palestinians%20by%20Donald%20Trump.%20He%20didn%E2%80%99t%20promise%20to%20reopen%20the%20PLO%20mission%20in%20Washington%20or%20the%20US%20embassy%20in%20East%20Jerusalem%2C%20which%20was%20established%20in%201844%20before%20being%20closed%20in%202019%20by%20Secretary%20of%20State%20Mike%20Pompeo%2C%20a%20man%20who%20once%20called%20Barack%20Obama%20an%20ISIS%20sympathizer.%20Blinken%20didn%E2%80%99t%20say%20that%20settlements%20violate%20international%20law%20%E2%80%94%20another%20longstanding%20US%20position%20that%20Trump%20overturned%20and%20the%20Biden%20administration%20has%20failed%20to%20restore.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20same%20month%20as%20Blinken%E2%80%99s%20J%20Street%20speech%2C%20there%20was%20another%20attempt%20to%20hold%20Israel%20accountable%20through%20the%20international%20legal%20framework.%20The%20UN%20General%20Assembly%20asked%20the%20International%20Court%20of%20Justice%20(ICJ)%20for%20an%20advisory%20opinion%20on%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20policies%20and%20practices%20of%20Israel%20in%20the%20occupied%20Palestinian%20territory.%E2%80%9D%20The%20United%20States%20voted%20against%20the%20referral%2C%20along%20with%20European%20states%20like%20Britain%20and%20Germany.%20In%20July%20of%20this%20year%2C%20the%20British%20government%20submitted%20a%20forty-three-page%20legal%20document%20to%20the%20ICJ%20urging%20it%20not%20to%20hear%20the%20case%20at%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20to%20the%C2%A0%3Cem%3EGuardian%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20a%20senior%20Palestinian%20source%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fworld%2F2023%2Faug%2F24%2Fuk-seeking-block-icj-ruling-israeli-occupation-palestine%5C%22%3Edescribed%20the%20document%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0as%20%E2%80%9Ca%20complete%20endorsement%20of%20Israeli%20talking%20points.%E2%80%9D%20Antony%20Blinken%20had%20previously%20objected%20to%20the%20ICC%20case%20on%20the%20grounds%20that%20the%20Palestinians%20%E2%80%9Cdo%20not%20qualify%20as%20a%20sovereign%20state.%E2%80%9D%20Now%20his%20British%20allies%20turned%20that%20argument%20on%20its%20head%20by%20presenting%20the%20occupation%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9Cbilateral%20dispute%E2%80%9D%20between%20states.%20The%20only%20consistent%20principle%20at%20work%20was%20the%20demand%20that%20Israel%20should%20enjoy%20complete%20impunity.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3C%2Fsection%3E%20%3Csection%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EClampdown%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIsrael%E2%80%99s%20backers%20in%20Europe%20and%20North%20America%20are%20equally%20hostile%20to%20the%20idea%20of%20pressure%20being%20applied%20through%20civil%20society.%20The%20Boycott%2C%20Divestment%2C%20and%20Sanctions%20(BDS)%20movement%20is%20an%20attempt%20to%20compensate%20for%20the%20refusal%20of%20governments%20to%20impose%20any%20sanctions%20on%20Israel%20for%20its%20oppression%20of%20the%20Palestinians.%20However%2C%20there%20have%20been%20repeated%20attempts%20to%20outlaw%20that%20movement%2C%20from%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.middleeasteye.net%2Fnews%2Fbds-israel-boycott-echr-favour-activists-france%5C%22%3EFrance%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0to%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hrw.org%2Fnews%2F2019%2F04%2F23%2Fus-states-use-anti-boycott-laws-punish-responsible-businesses%5C%22%3EUnited%20States%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cq%3EThe%20hostile%2C%20authoritarian%20response%20to%20legal%20and%20civil%20society%20initiatives%20from%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20Western%20allies%20shows%20us%20what%20they%20really%20want%20from%20the%20Palestinians.%3C%2Fq%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMost%20recently%2C%20the%20UK%20parliament%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rs21.org.uk%2F2023%2F07%2F12%2Fpalestine-solidarity-the-anti-bds-bill-and-the-security-state%2F%5C%22%3Epassed%20a%20bill%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0that%20bans%20public%20bodies%20such%20as%20local%20councils%20from%20making%20any%20decisions%20about%20procurement%20or%20investment%20based%20on%20%E2%80%9Cpolitical%20or%20moral%20disapproval%20of%20foreign%20state%20conduct.%E2%80%9D%20In%20theory%2C%20this%20would%20oblige%20councils%20to%20do%20business%20with%20any%20state%20in%20the%20world%2C%20not%20just%20Israel%2C%20regardless%20of%20%E2%80%9Cpolitical%20or%20moral%20disapproval.%E2%80%9D%20But%20the%20bill%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpublications.parliament.uk%2Fpa%2Fbills%2Fcbill%2F58-03%2F0325%2F220325.pdf%5C%22%3Eallows%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0the%20British%20government%20to%20grant%20a%20waiver%20from%20this%20rule%20in%20almost%20every%20case%2C%20with%20the%20exceptions%20of%20%E2%80%9C(a)%20Israel%2C%20(b)%20the%20Occupied%20Palestinian%20Territories%2C%20or%20(c)%20the%20Occupied%20Golan%20Heights.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20other%20words%2C%20the%20British%20authorities%20make%20no%20distinction%20in%20law%20between%20Israel%20as%20it%20was%20before%20the%201967%20war%20and%20the%20occupied%20territories%20beyond%20the%20so-called%20Green%20Line.%20This%20is%20certainly%20the%20way%20the%20way%20Israeli%20politicians%20see%20things%3A%20they%20have%20made%20it%20clear%20time%20and%20time%20again%20that%20they%20consider%20the%20West%20Bank%20settlements%20to%20be%20an%20integral%20part%20of%20the%20Israeli%20state%20and%20have%20no%20intention%20of%20dismantling%20them%20at%20any%20point%20in%20the%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Caside%3E%3C%2Faside%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20hostile%2C%20authoritarian%20response%20to%20legal%20and%20civil%20society%20initiatives%20from%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20Western%20allies%20shows%20us%20what%20they%20really%20want%20from%20the%20Palestinians.%20They%20don%E2%80%99t%20just%20want%20the%20Palestinian%20national%20movement%20to%20refrain%20from%20using%20violence%20against%20Isr