om%2F277825%2Fbeach-clean-up-mangrove-plantation-climate-change-odisha-security-guard-eco-warrior%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emangrove%20saplings%3C%2Fa%3E%20each%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EEdited%20by%20Pranita%20Bhat%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696860075000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F%3Fp%3D331813%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Murukesan%2C%20known%20as%20the%20%E2%80%98Mangrove%20Man%E2%80%99%20in%20his%20community%20in%20Kochi%2C%20discovered%20the%20vital%20link%20between%20declining%20mangroves%20and%20increasing%20cyclones%20along%20the%20coastline.%20A%20decade%20ago%2C%20he%20embarked%20on%20a%20mission%20to%20plant%20mangroves%20along%20Kerala's%20shorelines%20and%20remains%20dedicated%20to%20this%20cause.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Krystelle%20Dsouza%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A19%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F331813%2Fkochi-murukesan-plants-lakhs-of-mangrove-along-kerala-coastline-video%2F%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%E2%80%98Mini%20Brazil%20of%20India%E2%80%99%20Was%20Once%20Infamous%20for%20Illegal%20Liquor%3A%20How%20One%20Man%20Transformed%20a%20Village%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EAlmost%20a%20decade%20ago%2C%20Bicharpur%20%E2%80%94%20a%20village%20in%20the%20tribal-dominated%20Shahdol%20district%20of%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20%E2%80%94%20was%20notorious%20for%20its%20rampant%20production%20of%20illicit%20liquor%20and%20narcotics.%20The%20primary%20source%20of%20income%20for%20many%20families%20was%20the%20production%20of%20liquor%20from%20the%20locally%20available%20%3Cem%3Emahua%20%3C%2Fem%3Efruit%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20this%20village%2C%20every%20house%20has%20been%20making%20%3Cem%3Ekachhi%20shat%20%3C%2Fem%3E(%3Cem%3Emahua%20%3C%2Fem%3Eliquor)%20for%20generations.%20They%20did%20not%20consider%20it%20wrong%20or%20illegal%20since%20it%20was%20deeply%20ingrained%20in%20their%20culture%20for%20a%20long%20time.%20Even%20children%2C%20regardless%20of%20their%20ages%2C%20were%20involved%20in%20this%20work.%20In%20fact%2C%20the%20villagers%2C%20including%20children%2C%20consumed%20liquor%20regularly%3B%20it%20was%20like%20their%20everyday%20tea%20and%20the%20medicine%20for%20any%20disease%2C%E2%80%9D%20Raees%20Ahmed%20tells%20%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Better%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20today%20the%20village%20has%20undergone%20a%20remarkable%20transformation%2C%20emerging%20as%20a%20hub%20for%20the%20rising%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F310340%2Fmumbai-resident-ashok-rathod-uses-football-to-help-slum-children-stay-in-school-oscar-foundation%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estars%20of%20football%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%20has%20produced%20around%2045%20state%20and%20national-level%20football%20players%20%E2%80%94%20including%20Sanya%20Kunde%2C%20Rajni%20Singh%2C%20Laxmi%20Sahis%2C%20Anil%20Singh%20Gond%2C%20and%20Hanuman%20Singh.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBecause%20every%20household%20in%20the%20village%20has%20a%20football%20player%2C%20it%20has%20come%20to%20be%20known%20as%20the%20%E2%80%98Mini%20Brazil%E2%80%99%20of%20Madhya%20Pradesh.%20The%20journey%20of%20Bicharpur%20village%20from%20its%20miserable%20state%20to%20%E2%80%98Mini%20Brazil%E2%80%99%20was%20orchestrated%20by%20former%20footballer%20and%20coach%20Raees%20Ahmed.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EAn%20unlikely%20football%20hub%3C%2Fh2%3E%20%3Cp%3ERaees%20says%20that%20the%20Shahdol%20division%20has%20been%20a%20football%20hub%20for%20nearly%20three%20generations.%20The%20tribal%20children%20grew%20up%20playing%20football%20but%20without%20any%20formal%20training.%20Raaes%2C%20who%20has%20been%20playing%20football%20since%20the%20age%20of%2010%2C%20was%20one%20of%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20used%20to%20learn%20football%20by%20seeing%20players%20in%20tournaments.%20But%20we%20did%20not%20have%20any%20formal%20training%20or%20guidance%20in%20the%20sport%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20the%2053-year-old%20who%20grew%20up%20following%20Diego%20Armando%20Maradona%20%E2%80%94%20a%20professional%20football%20player%20from%20Argentina.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%20%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2Ffootball-bicharpur-5-1696858393.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20tribal%20children%20grew%20up%20playing%20football%20but%20without%20any%20formal%20training.%20%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2Ffootball-bicharpur-5-1696858393.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2Ffootball-bicharpur-5-1696858393-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2Ffootball-bicharpur-5-1696858393-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2Ffootball-bicharpur-5-1696858393-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2Ffootball-bicharpur-5-1696858393-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-331820%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EEarlier%2C%20the%20tribal%20children%20grew%20up%20playing%20football%20but%20without%20any%20formal%20training.%20%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhen%20Raees%20was%20in%20Class%208%2C%20he%20recalls%2C%20he%20played%20in%20the%20%E2%80%98under%2019%E2%80%99%20category%20at%20the%20national%20level.%20He%20went%20on%20to%20play%20football%20professionally%20at%20the%20national%20level%20seven%20times%20during%20his%20career.%20After%20graduating%20with%20a%20Bachelor%20of%20Arts%20in%201995%2C%20he%20secured%20a%20job%20